+**Required fix**: Add an idempotency property â€” `evaluate_program` must produce the same classification if run twice with the same inputs, even if state file is mid-write. One approach: after marking a lane `Failed` due to staleness, record the detection timestamp in the state file atomically, so a subsequent load can distinguish "never checked" from "checked and found stale."
 
